# RSON Shared-Code Open License v1.0 (Draft)

**Copyright © Twerse Shared Enterprise (51% Portfolio Company, 49% Contributor Community)**

---

## 1. Preamble
RSON is an open, universal data format.  
This license ensures free adoption while maintaining shared governance under **Twerse**.  

---

## 2. Granted Rights
- Free reading, usage, and implementation of RSON in all **non-commercial** projects.  
- Modifications or extensions permitted for internal use.  
- Redistribution of implementations permitted **under this same license**.  

---

## 3. Obligations
- All modifications or extensions of RSON must be shared publicly through Twerse’s official infrastructure.  
- Redistributed implementations must include this license.  
- Contributors assign economic rights to Twerse in exchange for a share of the **49% collective pool**.  

---

## 4. Restrictions
- Commercial use prohibited without a complementary license (*Shared-Code Valorized*).  
- Prohibited to redistribute RSON under another name.  
- Prohibited to patent any part of the RSON format.  

---

## 5. Governance
- **Twerse** retains responsibility for the official evolution of RSON.  
- Community contributions are integrated through the governance charter (51% Portfolio, 49% Contributors).  

---

## 6. Warranty
RSON is provided **“as is”**, without warranties of any kind.  
Twerse and contributors are not liable for damages resulting from its use.  
